13/05/2007
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Cyprus President Tassos Papadopoulos named on Friday (May 11th) Christodoulos Pasiardis as new defence minister.
Pasiardis will take over the post, vacant since the death of Nikos Symeonidis last week.
Papadopoulos' aide Vassilis Palmas would be the Cypriot cabinet's new spokesman.
(Kathimerini - 12/05/07;
CNA - 11/05/07)
